body:
There are two bugs on ZeroMq:
1. zsys_init: Assertion `!s_process_ctx' failed
2. zsock_connect( ) fail for inproc communication

The first one is caused by multiple threads calling zsys_init function concurrently.  ZeroMQ restricts the order of binding and connect for inproc communication. 
http://api.zeromq.org/4-0:zmq-connect says that "The first exception is when using the inproc:// transport: you must call zmq_bind() before calling zmq_connect()."

http://api.zeromq.org/4-0:zmq-connect says that "The first exception is when using the inproc:// transport: you must call zmq_bind() before calling zmq_connect()."
The second one is because the endpoint to connect has not bind yet. The comments for zsys_init is as follows,
//  Initialize CZMQ zsys layer; this happens automatically when you create
//  a socket or an actor; however this call lets you force initialization
//  earlier, so e.g. logging is properly set-up before you start working.
//  Not threadsafe, so call only from main thread. Safe to call multiple
//  times. Returns global CZMQ context.
Hence, we need to call zsys_init in the main thread before starting sub-threads, e.g., by creating a socket using zsock_new.
